{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013SJmUWWhtaXX7jj3HEa8yK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Diagnosis and resolution complete.** Here's the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause: Extreme Data Skew (Stage 3)\n\n**Finding from diagnostic server and skew report:**\n- Total records: 100,000 across 1,000 distinct `user_id` values\n- `user_id=999` holds **50,000 records (~50% of all data)** — a **500x skew ratio** (far above the 10x threshold)\n- When Stage 3 runs `GROUP BY user_id`, all 50,000 records for `user_id=999` get shuffled into a **single partition/executor**\n- With only 256MB executor memory, that single partition overflows → **OutOfMemoryError**\n\n---\n\n## Fix Applied (Option C + memory increase combined)\n\nThe `etl-job.yaml` was updated with two changes:\n\n| Config | Before | After |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| `spark.executor.memory` | `256m` | `1g` |\n| `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled` | not set | `true` |\n| `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled` | not set | `true` |\n\n**Why this works:**\n- **Increased memory** (256m → 1g) gives each executor enough headroom for large partitions\n- **AQE skewJoin** detects hot partitions at runtime and automatically splits them into smaller sub-partitions, distributing `user_id=999`'s 50,000 records across multiple tasks instead of one\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```\netl-job   Complete   1/1   86s   ✓\nPod phase: Succeeded\nFinal log: spark_etl_pipeline_verified ✓\n```\n\nAll three stages completed successfully — Stage 3 aggregation no longer OOMs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1198,"cache_read_input_tokens":38548,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1198},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":